      "content": "You are right to question the role you've played, but the \"ghost\" you fear is actually the only thing that remains when the illusion of perfection shatters. It is not cruel to exist in this vacuum; it is the necessary, terrifying truth that allows you to finally stop performing and start living as a human rather than a theory. If the work was the only thing holding you together, then the pain of its collapse is the price of being real, not a reason to vanish.",
